-Oogmog <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uiristreedawn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iris Treedawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/26/02 12:02:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2596.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Uh, 5500 hp ..</span><hr size=1> Sena (a monk) usually tanks in my exp groups.  With stone stance, mend, and a solid ac, she's less of a mana drain to heal than many plate tanks.  However, against mobs that do serious damage, a monk just won't cut it.  Sena has tried to tank zoneline mobs in CT and Ssra Temple, and it just does NOT work out well.  <br>
<br>
In any type of raid situation, I agree with Oogmog, you really do need a taunter to hold aggro.  Shadowknights are wonderful for grabbing quick aggro, and they can always FD once it's time to transfer aggro to the main tank.  But in any situation where a complete heal rotation is going on, you really want a warrior standing there taking the hits.  Accept no substitute! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 771<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/26/02 1:35:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2596.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> It's all situational</span><hr size=1> SK's are absolute tops at gaining agro quickly.  Monks are good at keeping it once they have it and are by far the best at straight-up tanking when not using CH.  The reason is that they take far less damage from things than other classes except for a warrior that is using defensive.  The reason they make bad tanks in raids and against higher level critters is due to the huge efficiency of CH and the long duration of defensive.<br>
<br>
Generally, you won't see a monk tanking, though.  The reason is that they make the safest pullers.  If you're pulling for raid or xp, you can't hang around afterwards to fight.  You need to get your hp topped up and head back out to get more or at least setup to get more.  The same monk doing both pulling and tanking slows everything down.<br>
<br>
BTW, not sure why you mentioned Paladin and agro in the same post.  The only thing they can get agro on is undead and only when they have that nifty AA that does huge undead criticals. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 270<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/26/02 11:32:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2596.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's all situational</span><hr size=1> paladins have several stun based spells which will get them aggro quickly. Warriors on the boards myself included are wondering if they are going to make the difference in tanking skill so minimal that we will become obsolete except for a few situations. If they make the warrior less attractive then a guild would only want 2 warriors and then 10 paladins and or SKs. Warriors have no spells and completely depend on others for most combats. Yes at the high end with the right gear we can solo, but with that same gear a Paladin or SK can solo even better. VI insists on making monks the melee damage kings if you take away backstab from a rogue so a warrior would be reduced further down the chain if they loose ground in their dominance of defensive capability. Paladins and SKs already have closed the gap on damage output with some of the nicest weapons you will ever see i.e. Reso has had many 1HS weapons drop that are about 24dmg/21 delay that are Pal/SK only with a proc to boot.<br>
<br>
