     Like enchanter visage, and stacks... so now we can cast hate spells on a warrior... and i am sure out of 2, 3 shadowknights that one of them can spare the room to memorise this spell.<br>
<br>
What was interesting was Warriors going into MA with a shield, and haveing a shadowknight use Agro spells to keep the warrior taunting, and also can stack with enchanter line i hear. The thing is, will this use a buff slot?<br>
<br>
How many shadowknights want to play giveing agro to warriors? quite frankly it is a rather painfull thing to do... to take something that you have clung onto feeling it the 'best' feature to others (not yourself) and then have you cast it on another warrior!!!! <br>
     Saying that, i 'would' use both those spells... because sometimes i suck up my pride and will use it to keep a warrior tanking, other times i want to take the odd hit and lifetap back. /shrug I still think it is either a HATE it or LOVE it type approach to class balance.<br>
